    "They are speedily making headway in education and are projected to increase more swiftly (Zhang & Aslan 2021).",
    "According to Munde (2023), AI in the Education market industry's compound annual growth rate (CAGR) is projected at 38% during the predicted period (2023) (2024) (2025) (2026) (2027) (2028) (2029) (2030).",
    "Clearly, more educational institutions now employ these tools because of their proven and potential benefits for teaching, learning, and research, substantiating Davis' (1989) TAM's claim that perceived usefulness triggers technology users to accept and utilise new technologies.",
